@node about " No_Password v1.3 by Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS"
@prev main
@{"°°" link grems}
   _____  _              _
  /  _  \| |__  ___ _  _| |_
 |   _   | '_ \/ _ \ || |  _|
 |__| |__|_.__/\___/\_,_|\__|                        @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 No Password is for those users who  forget their password and want to get
 back on the BBS. This door allows the (l)user to log-in under a fake user
 name you have created and leave a  private msg to the SysOp with details,
 so the SysOp (if he really wants too) can contact the user and advice (or
 laugh and abuse) them of their password, and in turn allow them back onto
 the BBS, if you really want them too!  Hopefully this is a rare activity?

 This is a tiny update from Version 1.2 of No_Password ('98).

 This door is dedicated to the Amiga and it's loyal owners... Hooray!

@endnode
@node run " No_Password v1.3 by Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS"
@{"°°" link grems}
  _____         _        _ _
 |_   _|_ _  __| |_ __ _| | |
  |   || ' \(_-<  _/ _` | | |
 |_____|_||_/__/\__\__,_|_|_|                        @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 Firstly (if you already haven't) create a new directory called "gremlins"
 in your doors directory. Assign "gremlins" to your doors path in the user
 startup sequence, eg: "assign gremlins: doors:gremlins" assuming you have
 the doors path assigned also, you annoying pain in the arse SysOp. ;o)

 Move the "No_Password" directory into the "gremlins" dir and run the door
 via the "Introdoor.text" sequence, eg: "gremlins/no_password/no_password"

 Firstly, you need to change line 7 in the MAXs text config,  which if you
 already haven't  changed  it says "Security Violation".  Delete this line
 and enter the following, "<gremlins:no_password/no_password.bbs"  without
 the quotes. "No_Password.bbs" is shown when the user screws up their pass
 word attempts, and explains what they need to do. Refer to file and see.

 Now go into the MAXs user editor and "create" a new user.  You have three
 options to what you call this fake user for the door to work. You can use
 either "Guest", "Idiot" or "Dummy". Put in a password you want to use and
 enter anything else for the rest of the fake user's details. Refer to the
 picture file "No_Password.iffpic" to get an idea and more info.

 That should be it, now to test it.  Log under the fake user's name, enter
 the password you assigned and you should be presented with the 1st screen
 which is "No_Password.text",  and then "No_Password.text2". Refer to both
 screens to understand what each one means or explains to the user. And if
 you wish, you may alter these sreens, etc..

 Do you understand?? Hmm, no..? @{"Contact" link call} me if need be..!? You will need to
 contact me to get your "own version" as No_Password is hard-coded with my
 name (Glen Martin), as the user has to  leave a msg to the almighty SysOp
 within the door.

@endnode
